''''CRAWFORD'''' is derived from the Gaelic "cru" meaning bloody , and "ford" meaning 'pass or crossing,' and is believed by most to mean a '''crossing of blood'''. 

Believed to be first assumed by the proprietor of the lands and barony of Crawford, in Lanarkshire, Scotland. 

A possible similar derivation comes from "crawe" meaning 'crow' and "ford" meaning 'pass or crossing.'

Crawford is of Scottish & Norman origin.

Alternate Surname Spellings: CROFFORD, CRAWFFORD, CRAUFURD, CRUFORD